author: Inside Edition
description: Eva's journey to Inside Edition started in local news. In 2016 she made the leap to ABC network news covering the top stories of our time and co-anchoring "Good Morning America Weekend." She most recently co-anchored GMA3. Now, following the departure of Deborah Norville, Eva is the new anchor of Inside Edition. Her first day on the job got a big welcome from Inside Edition's staff and weekend anchor Mary Calvi.
title: Inside Edition Welcomes Eva Pilgrim as New Host

author: Inside Edition
description: Influencers sat down at a table at a restaurant and just before they were about to take their first bites, a car crashed through the restaurant, striking their table. The glass shattered and the impact knocked them over. Influencers Nina Unrated and Patrick Blackstone try amazing meals around town but they never expected this. They were rushed to the hospital with cuts. It happened inside Cuvee's Culinary Creations in Houston.
title: Car Crashes Into Houston Restaurant and Strikes Table of Influencers

author: Inside Edition
description: Ukraine's President Zelenskyy is back at the White House and this time he wore a suit. On his last infamous visit, Zelenskyy was called out for wearing his signature informal attire. Monday, that same journalist who called him out apologized. Then, Zelenskyy delivered this zinger: "and you are in the same suit." According to one report, Zelenskyy was asked by the White House to wear a suit. Zelenskyy was accompanied by leaders from across Europe.
title: White House Reportedly Asked Zelenskyy to Wear Suit to White House

author: Inside Edition
description: Rebecca claims she was changing 7-month-old Emmanuel Haro's diapers in the parking lot outside a sporting goods store when he was kidnapped. She says the baby was in the back seat of her car and she was standing by the door when she heard the voice of a stranger and was struck from behind. She has stopped talking to detectives. "Rebeccas was confronted with inconsistencies in her initial statement and declined to continue the interview," police said.
title: Police Find 'Inconsistencies' After Mom Claims Baby was Kidnapped

author: Inside Edition
description: It took less than two minutes for these thieves to make off with two million dollars worth of merchandise after they struck a jewelry store in Seattle. Police say four masked men smashed their way into the locked West Seattle store using hammers. Once inside, police say one suspect brandished a can of bear spray and a taser to keep employees under control. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: $2 Million in Jewelry Stolen During 90-Second Heist in Seattle: Cops

author: Inside Edition
description: A Nigerian man says he came up with a way he hopes will make farming less laborious. Shamsudeen Jibril, 25, is an aerospace engineering graduate. It's a much different career path from his father, who was a civil servant and farmer. He created this unmanned aerial vehicle, which can spray crops with pesticides as well as detect any diseases that might be going around the fields. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Drone Helps Farmers Detect Disease in Crops and Give Treatment
